text: Madison County is a county in the U.S. state of New York. As of the 2020 census, 68,016 people lived there. The county seat is Wampsville. The county was founded in 1806 and named after James Madison, fourth President of the United States of America. ==References== Category:1800s establishments in New York (state) Category:1806 establishments in the United States Category:New York (state) counties
title: Madison County, New York
